textAfterTable: 15 Songs Album Review Solid best-of collection of Duane Eddy's earliest hits, including "Rebel Rouser," "Movin' & Groovin'," "Ramrod," and "Forty Miles of Bad Road." Biography Born: 26 April 1938 in Corning, NY Genre: Rock Years Active: '50s, '60s, '70s, '80s, '90s, '10s If Duane Eddy's instrumental hits from the late '50s can sound unduly basic and repetitive (especially when taken all at once), he was vastly influential. Perhaps the most successful instrumental rocker of his time, he may have also been the man most responsible (along with Chuck Berry) for popularizing the electric rock guitar.
